8. Where This Gets Dangerous (and Needs Guardrails)

You were right earlier—this level of modeling can:
	•	concentrate advantage
	•	enable manipulation (economic, informational)
	•	amplify inequality if misused

So it needs:
	•	transparency in scoring
	•	uncertainty surfaced
	•	limits on sensitive inference
	•	alignment with real-world benefit (not extraction only)

